The C Permit is available to all registered students and those auditing classes at the university. This permit allows students to park in any C lots from 6 A.M. to 4 A.M. daily. Longhorn Lots are also available with this permit 24/7 unless otherwise indicated by signs. This permit does not have a limit on sales so parking becomes more challenging throughout the day as spaces are taken.

The C+ Permit is available to all registered students and those auditing classes at the university. This permit allows students to park in any C lots from 6 A.M. to 4 A.M. daily. Longhorn Lots are also available with this permit 24/7 unless otherwise indicated by signs. This permit also allows students to park in all university garages (except CCG) between 5 P.M. and 4 A.M. weekly and all day on weekends (Friday at 5 P.M. to Monday at 4 A.M.). This permit does not have a limit on sales so parking becomes more challenging throughout the day as spaces are taken.

The R Permit is available to any UT Austin student who has a UT Housing and Food Residence Hall contract. Garage permits offer the most convenient parking options for residence halls with many of our garages next to, or across the street from, university housing. R permits are valid only in the garage for which they are purchased. Only limited numbers of R permits are sold, meaning that in general you should always be able to find a parking space. R parking is restricted to the upper level of the garages Monday-Friday, but a majority of the spaces available are covered. Nonetheless, you might be required to park on the roof at times during the term for your permit. This permit should provide parking for you in your assigned garage 24/7, with few exceptions. Occasionally, R permit holders may be relocated to accommodate large events. Advanced e-mail notifications will be sent and in general, you can expect to be relocated to another garage. Longhorn Lots are also available for all permits.

The S Permit is available to UT students who live off campus (i.e., those who do NOT have an official university residence hall contract). S permits are valid only in the garage for which they are purchased. Only limited numbers of S permits are sold, meaning that in general you should always be able to find a parking space. S parking is restricted to the upper level of the garages Monday-Friday, but a majority of the spaces available are covered. Nonetheless, you might be required to park on the roof at times during the term for your permit. This permit should provide parking for you in your assigned garage 24/7, with few exceptions. This permit is not intended for habitual overnight storage of your vehicle, and this will cost an additional storage fee. Occasionally, S permit holders may be relocated to accommodate large events. Advanced e-mail notifications will be sent and in general, you can expect to be relocated to another garage. Longhorn Lots are also available for all permits.

The M Permit is available to any affiliate of the university. Intended for use with a motorcycle, motor scooter, moped, or motor-assisted bicycles. M permit holders may only park in designated motorcycle parking areas from 7:30 a.m. to 3:30 p.m. They may park in surface lot automobile spaces after permit restrictions have lifted as indicated by signs; they may not park at any time in automobile garage spaces. Vehicle must be parked perpendicular to the curb when applicable. Longhorn Lots are available with this permit weekdays after 3:30 p.m. and weekends from Friday at 3:30 p.m. to Monday at 7:30 a.m.

The N Permit is available to students, faculty, staff, and other affiliates. N permit holders may park in spaces for \"Any UT Permit\", and Longhorn Lots. Times restricted to weeknights between 5:45 p.m. and 7:30 a.m. and all day on weekends from Friday at 5:45 p.m. to Monday at 7:30 a.m. (unless otherwise indicated by signs â€” Note: some Longhorn Lots have no parking between 4 a.m. and 6 a.m.).

The N+ Permit is available to students, faculty, staff, and other affiliates. Parking is not guaranteed in any particular garage, but is accessible for all garages (except the Conference Center Garage - CCG) weeknights between 5 p.m. and 4 a.m. and all day on weekends (Friday at 5 p.m. to Monday at 4 a.m.) on a space-available basis. Additionally, the N+ Permit grants access to park in Longhorn Lots and spaces signed \"Any UT Permit\" weeknights between 5:45 p.m. and 7:30 a.m. and all day on weekends (Friday at 5:45 p.m. to Monday at 7:30 a.m.).
